                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/3510: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-31T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 31, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>529. Department’s 240, August 29, 7 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] p.m. I have
                    repeated this message to Tsingtao for his guidance adding the statement that in
                    view of increased activity on the part of guerrillas in Shantung it appears to
                    the Embassy unwise to encourage return of Americans to interior points at this
                    time and I suggest that you warn Americans that they return at their own risk.
                    Peiping informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
